    {
      "id": "entry-surfaces-entries",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Named Entry Surfaces",
      "position": {
        "x": 380,
        "y": 140
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Named Entry Surfaces\n\nA graph should be able to declare stable entry handles such as:\n- `open`\n- `expand`\n- `summary`\n\nPorts point to the graph and a handle, not to arbitrary internal node ids.",
